  "text": "The equation (1) may also consist regularization terms [CITATION_1] and becomes: In [CITATION_2] the authors proposed an effective implicit representation for evolving curves and surfaces, which has found many applications, because it allows for automatic change of topology such as merging and breaking, and the calculations are made on a fixed rectangular grid. A given curve C is represented by zero level set of a scalar Lipschitz continuous function ",
